is not powerfull just don't use them often or are in a guilde that only do mobs that they can kill easily. For my guild Mod rod 2 makes alot of encounters that otherwise would have been impossible, very doable. I am in a medium sized guild, we don't have alot of clerics, no primal weapons. However we were able to take down zelnithak with 15 persons (2 clerics), The va dyn with less than 2 groups (only on cleric this fight).<br>
Each time the key of the success is we had a mage with Trods. When we are a bit low for a target, then i know i must do 100% rods. Then Trods are really powerfull. For Vindikator 4 mages just drop rods. If you always have 10 clerics with FT15 and 4500 mana pool online then yes Trod are cool but not really powerfull.<br>
1 Trod is almost the same mana cost as sofb and allows 1.5 CH. Do you really want this mana flying on a nuke that could be resisted?? Not always. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sirellyn>Sirellyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(4/23/02 6:08:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=191.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Replies</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Trod IS powerfull on raids, does that mean that it should be nerfed? No imho. For god sake, mages have one really efficient way to contribute to raids don't nerf it. Why do magician always want to nerf all the things that are a little bit more powerfull that their average spells. Is it that magician are soo used to mediocres nukes on raids and very low ability to contribute ? CH, KEI, AE bard songs are also very powerfull. So nerf them too. All those that think that mod rod 2 is not powerfull just don't use them often or are in a guilde that only do mobs that they can kill easily. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah I'm agreeing it gives us a really powerful ability.  Consider, FT 15 + Bard song + KEI + Transons + Water elemental form.<br>
<br>
Pretty sick regen right?  How long do you think it would take you to get to FM?  I'm thinking 2-3 minutes.<br>
<br>
Now you have a mod rod 2 spell and some divine light or celestial heal spells.  Having experience here, I can tell you it only takes 45 seconds or so.  If your cleric friend is down too much mana, give him a mod rod and that usually more than makes up for any he lost on you.  Net loss, about 400 mana at worst, going from 0 (after casting the first mod rod) to full.<br>
<br>
So... that ONE ability is better than a 60th level enchanter WITH a very hard to get spell, a 60th level bard with his spell, better than finding 15 points worth of flowing thought.  (Only Jaytee so far I know has done this, so this isn't obviously an easy thing, not to mention wasting all the slots.)  beats another one of your specific regenerations spells, with the addition of about 32 points of alternate experience to get a minor regen.<br>
<br>
Remember also that enchanters and bards have been specifically known since their creation to help a lot in mana regen.  We have not.  We've had next to nothing, until recently.<br>
<br>
So that one spell plus any sort of half decent healer beats all that.<br>
<br>
Doesn't that seem a teeeenie bit unbalanced?<br>
<br>
As for mages always wanting to nerf our own stuff.  I haven't heard anythign about it.  Maybe you can point me to some threads.  The only case I can even remotely think of is when people suggesting AFK XP is too cheesy.  Which we all know it is, and is an exploit to.<br>
<br>
One last note.  When taking stuff out of the game (nerfing) designers always should weigh what was lost by adding something back for the class.  Even if it's just something thats really neat.  It depends on how much power the class was assumed to be over.  So I'm saying if they do take this out they better as heck add something back in for us that reinforces our raid usefulness by approximately the same amount, but this time more towards our conceptual vision.   I don't care if it's summoning special bane weapons or more useful pets.<br>
<br>
But if designers are going to look back at mages and say we don't need a change because of our usefulness in raids which is consequently based mainly on this one spell, and call of the hero then I'd rather get the spell nerfed and over with so we have some more leverage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sirellyn>Sirellyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(4/23/02 6:15:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=191.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Replies</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
